
Observed Color,NDCI Value Range,Interpretation (Chl-a Level),Water Quality Implication
Deep Blue / Purple,Low (≈−0.1 to 0.05),Very Low Concentration.,"Very clean water with minimal phytoplankton/algae. This is expected in cold, fast-moving rivers."
Green / Yellow-Green,Medium (≈0.05 to 0.15),Moderate Concentration.,"Typical water quality. Indicates a measurable amount of chlorophyll-a, which is normal for a river environment."
Yellow / Orange,High (≈0.15 to 0.20),High Concentration.,"Elevated algal biomass. Could indicate high primary productivity or a localized area of algal accumulation (e.g., slow-moving water, an eddy)."
Bright Red,Very High (≈0.20+),Very High Concentration (Bloom).,Strong indication of an algal bloom. These areas warrant attention as they represent the highest chlorophyll levels detected.

